RECITALS: A. The Co-Tenants are each separately developing and will each separately construct, own and operate electricity generation and transmission projects, including photovoltaic energy generation projects, on real property in Kern County, California. B. 54KR’s energy project includes photovoltaic modules, inverters, and related infrastructure (the “54KR Project”) to be located approximately on the real property described on Exhibit A-1 attached hereto (the “54KR Project Site”). 67RK’s energy project includes photovoltaic modules, inverters, and related infrastructure (the “67RK Project”) and will be located approximately on the real property described on Exhibit A-2 attached hereto (the “67RK Project Site”). 65HK’s energy project includes photovoltaic modules, inverters, and related infrastructure (the “65HK Project”) and will be located approximately on the real property described on Exhibit A-3 attached hereto (the “65HK Project Site”). 87RL’s energy project includes photovoltaic modules, inverters, and related infrastructure (the “87RL Project”) and will be located approximately on the real property described on Exhibit A-4 attached hereto (the “87RL Project Site”). C. From time to time herein, the Co-Tenants’ respective project sites described above may be each individually referred to as a “Project Site,” and collectively referred to as the “Project Sites,” and the Co-Tenants’ respective projects described above are each individually referred to as a “Project”, and collectively as the “Projects”. D. Each Co-Tenant holds or shall hold its own individual real property rights (by fee ownership, lease, easement, right of way, or otherwise) to its respective Project Site. E. Various Co-Tenants are also holders of, or are acquiring certain lease, easement, license and permit rights, all of which are more particularly described on Exhibit B-1 (the “Shared Premises Agreements”), to use certain real property more particularly described on Exhibit B-2 (as amended and supplemented from time to time, and together with the Franchise Premises, the “Shared Premises”). Various Co-Tenants will require the use and possession of specified portions of the Shared Premises for the construction, operation, and maintenance of their respective Projects. F. Franchise Holder is the Grantee (as defined below) under the Franchise Agreement (as defined below), and 54KR is the Grantee under the 54KR Franchise Agreement (as defined below). Pursuant to the Franchise Agreement (in the case of Franchise Holder) and the 54KR Franchise Agreement (in the case of 54KR), Franchise Holder and 54KR each have the right to use certain real property more particularly described on Exhibit B-3 (as amended and supplemented from time to time, the “Franchise Premises”) for the construction, installation, operation, and maintenance of certain electrical transmission facilities, and the Parties wish to establish the terms and conditions of the management of and access to the Franchise Premises, of Franchise Holder’s exercise of its rights and obligations as Grantee under the Franchise Agreement and of 54KR’s exercise of its rights and obligations as Grantee under the 54KR Franchise Agreement. G. The Co-Tenants’ use of the Shared Premises shall also include the construction, operation, and maintenance of certain common infrastructure facilities supporting the construction, operation and maintenance of their respective Projects, including electrical transmission facilities, operations and maintenance facilities, access roads, and lay-down and staging areas for construction, all more particularly described below as the “Shared Facilities.” H. The Co-Tenants wish to set forth herein their respective rights and obligations regarding the joint design, procurement, development, construction, installation, ownership, use, maintenance, repair, replacement of, and additions to the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises. I. The Co-Tenants also wish to contract with Manager for the provision of certain limited services to be performed at the pleasure of the Co-Tenants with respect to the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises, and the Manager wishes to accept said engagement, on the terms and conditions contained herein. J. Franchise Holder, 67RK, 65HK, 87RL and Manager have entered into that certain Second Amended and Restated Redwood Solar Farm Project Shared Facilities Agreement dated as of December 17, 2015 (the “Original Agreement”). K. The Parties desire to amend and restate the Original Agreement as of the Effective Date on the terms and conditions set forth herein.
